GASTROENTERITIS - NORWAY (02): (BUSKERUD) CHRISTMAS PARTY
*********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 18 Dec 3012
From: Joanne Michelle Ocampo [edited]
<jfo36@georgetown.edu>


As of 18 Dec 2012, the county doctor of Ringerike County, the Norwegian Food Safety Authority, the Norwegian Institute of Public Health, and hotel officials from Klekken hotel were still investigating the outbreak associated with cases of gastroenteritis in Buskerud, Norway, that occurred between 5 and 9 Dec 2012.

An estimated 170 cases were initially reported, but on Sun 16 Dec 2012 the number of cases was adjusted to 319, 6 of whom have been hospitalised. The county doctor noted that symptoms caused by norovirus infection usually resolve 2 to 3 days post-infection, but that during this outbreak a number of patients have remained symptomatic for more than a week following the initial reports of disease.

Epidemiological survey methods indicate that the nature of this outbreak is food/waterborne, but that the source remains unknown. Analyses are under way, however, officials have noted that potential sources of contamination may already have been discarded and/or consumed.

For original articles (in Norwegian), please see:
http://www.mattilsynet.no/mat/nyhetsarkiv/sykdomsutbrudd_p__kl_kken_hotell_106325
